  m_RaycastPadding: {x: 0, y: 0, z: 0, w: 0}
  m_Maskable: 1
  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: "Master always told his son \u2014 \"The beginning, your foundation, is
    everything in life.\"\n\n\n\n\n\n\nThis note would serve as a record of our research
    progression, beginning 1989/07/04. At 04:04 PM I was ordered by the master to
    document all progress so that he may revisit it whenever he wishes.\n\n\n\n\n\nAt
    1989/07/20, sixteen days have passed. Researcher Olivier was disposed of two
    days ago after promising progress within a week. Nothing came of it.\n\n\n\n\nKlaus
    Bauer, a doctor from Germany. Though largely unknown and young, his prior research
    touches upon the very subject we pursue. We will run him through a series of
    evaluations before any consideration is made to appoint him as head researcher.\n\n\n\n\nReviews
    were conducted. At 1990/03/18 Klaus Bauer was appointed head researcher. The
    decision was met with quiet unease among the senior staff \u2014 a young outsider
    placed above them without warning. It was the master's call. Neither of us holds
    much confidence in it.\n\n\n\n\nThis is insanity \u2014 it is almost impossible
    to believe. Klaus Bauer has achieved in two months what our finest could not
    manage in years. The master has become hopeful for the first time in a long while.\n\n\n\n\nAt
    1992/03/10 its been 30 days since the last time master read these entries, and
    he no longer permits me inside the laboratories. Since Bauer's breakthrough,
    the two have grown inseparable \u2014 speaking behind closed doors, shutting
    everyone else out. It feels as though project ------ has been hollowed out and
    repurposed. I no longer recognize what we are working toward.\n\n\n\n\nSuch blasphemy!
    Yesterday I uncovered the truth of what the master now intends. He and Klaus
    Bauer wish to build an army of ------. That is what project ------ has been reduced
    to.\n\n\n\n\n\nThe master has decided to use me as a test subject. I was told
    by the young master, who delivered the news laughing. The master was not always
    this way \u2014 he was corrupted, hollowed out by the influence of Klaus Bauer.
    I write this knowing he will never read it. But I write it still.\n\n\n\n\nto
    solve the padlock puzzle .i have changed the lock password of the emergency electricity
    padlock. to the month and day of the last time the master read this note\n"
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
